As you can see between each "Iteration" there is several random values of "dividend_i" and "divisor_i" as expected.

However, when I open the resulting wave file in gtkwave, it shows this:
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2dcac6c7-52ef-4c57-a86e-32c296859220)

The "dividend_i" and "divisor_i" signals only change around valid cycles and the inner loop doesn't seem to take effect. What's even stranger, the debug signal "dividend_reg" which is just a delayed copy of "dividend_i" is changing in every cycle (and isn't delayed).

This is really my first time trying out the Verilator so it might be some kind of a stupid mistake on my side, but I couldn't find any existing article on how to solve it. I'd be happy if you could tell me what I'm doing wrong.

